  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Hyperphosphatemia is a severe complication to chronic kidney disease (CKD) and is associated
      with increased risk of vascular calcification, cardiovascular morbidity and mortality. Early
      dietary intervention and improvement in dietary therapy might optimally reduce cardiovascular
      complications. For this purpose we have investigated patients with CKD stage 3-4, their
      dietary habits, developed a New Nordic Renal Diet and investigated the short term effect on
      phosphorus homeostasis.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
